review_blob: Golden pour on tap at the bar. Nice taste. Not too sweet but definite presence of orange and citrus. Much better alternative than any other lager at the bar.

A combination of hoppiness and an unfiltered weisse that is amazing. I love this combination and this might be one of my favorite beers by Brooklyn. There is a distinct smell of hops from first whiff, but they are not overwhelming, allowing the entire beer to be balanced perfectly. A strong 8.5%.
On tap at DLD2008. Rich amber body with a while head. Aroma was filled with hops and mild fruit. Tasted great, with hints of  citrus. Smooth finish. A nice change from the thickness of the Dark Lord.
beer_name: Three Floyds Pride & Joy Mild Ale

review_blob: Got this 2007 Dark Lord on tap at DLD 2008. Looked very dark with a burnt orange tint to the head. Smelled of soy sauce and swirled like a syrup. First taste was thick and dark but smooth and delicious. Great tasting beer, but it coated my stomach. One beer was enough for me, but since this beer is so rare, I would drink it over and over again.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Great Scottish ale! Got it on tap at DLD2008. Dark, rich body with a smooth, malty finish. Most Scottish ales are usually too malty for me, but this one was blended perfectly.
beer_name: Three Floyds Robert The Bruce Scottish Ale

review_blob: An extremely hoppy IPA. The hops can be smelt from a mile away and as soon as it hits your tongue, it wont be forgotton. A true beer for hop lovers with a full body.
One of my favorite Goose Island brews. Thick, golden body and a sweet, fruity aroma traditional of wheat beers. Great unfiltered blend that lingers.
My favorite of the Budweiser line. Best taste of all of them and the least fattening. Not nearly as watered down as the rest of the American Lagers.
Personally, I prefer the Select, but there is nothing like an original Bud. First beer my father ever let me try.
Of all the light american beers, this one is my favorite. If I need a great session beer, better go with one that "tastes great, and is less filling!"
Never had a sextuple before, and this beer was insane! Full golden body, strong aroma. The alcohol was hidden well in the smell, but upon the taste, it is very prevalent. Very sweet but very strong.

Tapped at Dark Lord Day 2008. Began the day with the flagship and was very impressed. Full orange body with white head. Smelled of strong hops and citrus flavors and went down smooth and clean. Not too hoppy but the presence is definitely there. Started my day off with high expectations!
